1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:10,189
*(Verse 1)*

2
00:00:10,339 --> 00:00:15,527
Busted out the screen door, sun was
sinking low,

3
00:00:15,677 --> 00:00:20,866
Two little plants in busted pots, nowhere
else to go.

4
00:00:21,016 --> 00:00:26,204
William’s leaves went yellow like a
roadside sign,

5
00:00:26,354 --> 00:00:31,543
That’s how he says, “I’m thirsty,” and I
say, “Fine.”

6
00:00:31,693 --> 00:00:36,881
*(Verse 2)*

7
00:00:37,031 --> 00:00:42,220
He’s got that bonsai patience, quiet kind
of grace,

8
00:00:42,370 --> 00:00:47,559
Never begs for water, just holds his
place.

9
00:00:47,709 --> 00:00:52,897
I got a bottle of food, says “Use once a
week,”

10
00:00:53,047 --> 00:00:58,236
But we don’t do rules, we don’t really
speak.

11
00:00:58,386 --> 00:01:03,574
*(Chorus)*

12
00:01:03,724 --> 00:01:08,913
Feelin’ free and easy with Dander near my
knee,

13
00:01:09,063 --> 00:01:14,251
Named him after Davinder, but he flakes
you see.

14
00:01:14,401 --> 00:01:19,590
Curled up leaves like pages in the wind,

15
00:01:19,740 --> 00:01:24,929
Just me and the green things I never quite
tend.

16
00:01:25,079 --> 00:01:30,267
*(Verse 3)*

17
00:01:30,417 --> 00:01:35,606
Dander leans like he’s got a story to
tell,

18
00:01:35,756 --> 00:01:40,944
Crooked but proud in that terra-cotta
shell.

19
00:01:41,094 --> 00:01:46,283
We’ve seen cold nights and windows freeze,

20
00:01:46,433 --> 00:01:51,621
But they stuck around like old melodies.

21
00:01:51,771 --> 00:01:56,960
*(Chorus)*

22
00:01:57,110 --> 00:02:02,299
Feelin’ free and easy with Dander near my
knee,

23
00:02:02,449 --> 00:02:07,637
Named him after Davinder but it’s dandruff
you see.

24
00:02:07,787 --> 00:02:12,976
William’s going gold, that’s my cue,

25
00:02:13,126 --> 00:02:18,314
Two plants and a window and not much to
do.

26
00:02:18,464 --> 00:02:23,653
*(Bridge)*

27
00:02:23,803 --> 00:02:28,991
Could’ve read the label, could’ve tried
real hard,

28
00:02:29,141 --> 00:02:34,330
But they like the mess — water rings and
disregard.

29
00:02:34,480 --> 00:02:39,669
No mist, no feeding, just room to be,

30
00:02:39,819 --> 00:02:45,007
And I swear those plants still believe in
me.

31
00:02:45,157 --> 00:02:50,346
*(Final Chorus)*

32
00:02:50,496 --> 00:02:55,684
Freedom’s just a quiet room with filtered
afternoon,

33
00:02:55,834 --> 00:03:01,023
William looking noble, Dander out of tune.

34
00:03:01,173 --> 00:03:06,361
Life rolls on, but I know what’s true

35
00:03:06,511 --> 00:03:11,700
Two pots of patience, and me just passing
through.
